                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13123655" author="jesse_yates" created="Sun, 9 Oct 2011 09:36:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch does not add any new unit test for avro server since everything in avro server seems to be just pass through functionality to the table admin. All the other functionality is covered already by TestAvroUtil.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13126126" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2011 20:36:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a good test to move out since its being flakey in 0.92 (though the why needs fixing).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good but when I did:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
mvn -DskipTests verify
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The new test did not run.  Is this me?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13126127" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2011 20:37:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Or is it just that verify will only run if skipTests is NOT set as per above?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13126190" author="jesse_yates" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2011 21:52:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hmmm, its looking like &apos;tests&apos; count as integration tests too. Checking on this...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13126196" author="jesse_yates" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2011 21:59:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;okay, here is the deal. To &lt;em&gt;just&lt;/em&gt; run integration tests, use:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
mvn failsafe:integration-test
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;to run the integration tests. And then&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
mvn failsafe:verify
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to verify the output results. That is when you will find out if the integration tests fail. &lt;br/&gt;
If you don&apos;t run the latter, then maven outputs success, even if you have integration test failures.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13126199" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2011 22:07:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Jesse, @Doug:&lt;br/&gt;
I think Jesse&apos;s comment @ 12/Oct/11 21:59 should be put into hbase book.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13126210" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2011 22:26:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Ted Agree.  Let me do it on commit.  Will commit in a while.  Thanks Jesse.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13273039" author="jesse_yates" created="Fri, 11 May 2012 04:53:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking invalid. With Keywals&apos; work on the different sized tests, we don&apos;t need to worry about this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
